Rating: 3
Light and delicious. I agree with others about tossing some lemon in with the arugula and definitely using fresh oregano. I dipped the chicken in flour, then egg, then the panko mix. I find that you get more of the coating to stick that way. I also mixed some lemon zest into the panko mixture. I was cooking 6 pieces of chicken, so I cooked three at a time and put in a 200 degree oven until the rest were finished. THEN I sprinkled them with the lemon juice. I thought it kind of "woke them up" after they had sat in the oven for a few minutes. I served it with spaghetti with browned butter and myzithra cheese, although the spinach linguine sounded good, too!!

