Really wonderful and easy! I used three boneless chicken breasts, cut longways into 1-inch wide strips , then pounded to 1/2-inch . The breading was delicious & didn't stick. I followed the recipie exactly and think the fresh oregano helps make it. Once we'd finished dinner tonight & the chicken had gotten a little cold I snuck a bite - WOW! Still crispy only cold and the coating was even more flavorful. It goes wonderfuly with the pasta mentioned and the arugula. I sprinkled some fresh lemon juice & s & p onto the arugula then drizzled the olive oil & mixed. I placed the finished chicken on top of the arugula as a salad alongside the pasta. The tang of the addidtional lemon in the arugula was wonderful with the crispy chicken. A real keeper & going into my permanent file.

